    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376448>
    dc:description "FIGURES 18–23. Habitats (18–19, 21, 23) and burrows (20, 22) of Orcevia species, with white arrows indicating where the specimens were collected (© 18. Weihang Wang; 19–23. Kun Yu). 18. O. deelemanae Yu & Zhang, sp. nov. in Xishuangbanna, Yunnan; 19, 23. O. proszynskii (Song, Gu & Chen, 1988) in Jianfengling, Hainan; 20, 22. O. zu Yu & Zhang, sp. nov. in Gongshan County, Yunnan; 21. O. sica (Wu & Yang, 2008) comb. nov. in Baoshan, Yunnan." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376448/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10376532>
    dc:description "FIGURES 238–245. Orcevia sica (Wu & Yang, 2008) comb. nov., holotype male (238), non-type male (240–242) and female (239, 243–245). 238–239. Habitus; 240–242. Palp; 243. Top part of vulva, show accessory glands; 244. Epigynum; 245. Vulva; in dorsal (238–239, 245), prolateral (241), retrolateral (242), ventral (240, 244) and top (243) view.Abbreviations:AG, accessory gland; LPT, lobe like protrusion of tegulum; VFB, ventral femoral bump of male palp." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10376532/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

